# Truegrynd – Supabase Guidelines

## Core Tables
| Table | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `profiles` | Extends auth.users — username, sex, age, weight, faction, streak |
| `challenges` | All challenges (official + UGC). `status`: pending/approved/rejected |
| `scores` | Score submissions per user per challenge |
| `faction_stats` | Materialized view or computed: total points per faction |

## Client Usage
- Always import from `@/lib/supabase` — never instantiate a new client
- All DB calls must handle errors — never assume success
- Use `.select()` with explicit column lists — never `select('*')` in production queries

## RLS (Row Level Security)
- All tables have RLS enabled
- `profiles`: users can read all, write only their own
- `challenges`: everyone can read approved ones; admins can write all
- `scores`: users can read all validated scores; write only their own

## Secrets & Environment
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` — safe to expose (client-side)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` — safe to expose (RLS enforced)
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` — server-side only, never in client code

## Score Submission Pattern
```ts
// Always check top 10% threshold before saving
const rank = await getScoreRank(challengeId, value);
const isElite = rank <= TOP_10_THRESHOLD;
if (isElite && !videoUrl) throw new ValidationError('Video required for elite scores');
```

## Realtime
- Use Supabase Realtime only for leaderboard updates on challenge detail page
- Unsubscribe on component unmount to avoid memory leaks
